2. It always calls `rule[1]` as a function (no type check)

Since `rules.unshift` is used, the last `addRule` call ends up first in the array. The last rule added before the loop is the uncountable words rule. So with the mutation, every word would go through the first rule's function with `(word, rule[0])`.

The first rule in the array (last added) is the uncountable nouns rule. Its function is `function(w) { return w }`. So with the mutation, `plural("cat", 2)` would return `"cat"` not `"cats"`.

